<para id="fs-id1167793450143">For the following exercises, use shells to find the volumes of the given solids. Note that the rotated regions lie between the curve and the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext>-axis</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> and are rotated around the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mtext>-axis</m:mtext><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<exercise id="fs-id1167793450164">
<problem id="fs-id1167793450166">
<para id="fs-id1167793450168"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>and</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></para>
