<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167793417112">
<term>method of cylindrical shells</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167793417118">a method of calculating the volume of a solid of revolution by dividing the solid into nested cylindrical shells; this method is different from the methods of disks or washers in that we integrate with respect to the opposite variable</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
